AGI - Pain and anger>. Today is the day of the protest after the death, Monday, of five workers in Casteldaccia>, in the province of Pelermo, while a sixth remains in very serious conditions.» They died in a saturated environment of gas >, product of fermentation of the slurry whose presence was foreseeable and did not escape, trying to save one another in the tank of the waste water lifting plant of via Nazionale dell'Amap, the aqueduct company of the Municipality > of Palermo; but one after the other have yielded, won by toxic gas, sulphur dioxide, and the absence of protection and masks, as it would have been ascertained. On the spot, the family rage. An investigation is coordinated by the Prosecutor of Termini Imerese, who is willing to take the plant.
&nbsp;
The provincial secretaries of Fillea, Filca, Feneal proclaimed 8 hours of strike > following the death of the workers, of whom three were building. A strike that is flanked by the general one of 4 hours of Cgil, Cisl and Uil for all other sectors, with a prefecture at 9 o'clock. "Of course things change or we will go on with the mobilizations, to claim safety in the yards," they say, "we cannot understand why all the necessary measures have not been foreseen for interventions where harmful gases, dangerous for public safety can occur. With this new tragedy, it certifies an emergency and state of war. Here the dead at work are multiplying day by day. To the prefect we ask the intervention of the institutions and to urge the table on health and safety that we have long asked".
&nbsp;
From the controls carried out at the bilateral authorities, add the unions, some of the workers "were under frames regarding the tasks that were taking place in the yard". Among the deceased also an interinal worker, workers "too often considered standard B workers". In fact there is a certainty: to kill the five workers and to reduce to the end of life the sixth colleague were the hydrogen sulphur elations>. And then another certain fact: the absence of devices and safety conditions. He is certainly the provincial commander of the firefighters of Palermo, Girolamo Bentivoglio Fiandra: "This tragedy would not have been there if all necessary and planned precautions were taken." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2 The survivor remains grave, "48 decisive hours"</h2>
The conditions of the colleague of the 5 workers who died in a tank of the lifting system of the sewerage of Casteldaccia remain very serious. They confirm it to AGI sources of the Policlinico of Palermo where it is admitted. The patient "is intubated and ventilated, in severe respiratory distress, for a hydrogen sulphur intoxication". The situation is very serious and if it remained alive is because, it is supposed, it was the last to enter the tub and the first to be extracted. "We do not know what organs are compromised - the same sources say - and the prognosis is absolutely reserved on life at 48 hours: within 48 hours we expect an evolution and we will see".
Names of victims
The workers who have lost their lives are Epiphany Alsace, 71 years old, Roberto Raneri 51 years old, Ignazio Giordano, 57 years old, Giuseppe La Barbera, Giuseppe Miraglia. Epifanio Assazia is the owner of the company Quadrifoglio Group. Giuseppe La Barbera (who should be the son of the owner of the GrouP Quadrifoglio) and Miraglia have not yet been known. A sixth worker is admitted in serious condition to the Palermo Polyclinic. A seventh involved in the tragedy remained unharmed. On the site of the incident, in via Nazionale, the families of the victims who cry, embrace and ask themselves out loudly "Why?" &nbsp;
<h2>The post of the municipality of Casteldaccia</h2>
The municipal administration of Casteldaccia expresses "its pain for the tragedy that is upsetting our community on this sad day. The families of the deceased workers". The Municipality of Casteldaccia writes on Facebook after the massacre of workers in the small center of the Palermitano.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Syndicate Lagalla, terrible pain
&nbsp;"A terrible pain for the tragedy that caused death on the work of the workers in Casteldaccia. Their families and their co-workers go the cordon and proximity of the municipal administration." So the mayor of Palermo Roberto Lagalla.
&nbsp;
<h2>Melons, make full light</h2>
&nbsp; "The news of the workers involved in the tragic accident in Casteldaccia, in the Palermo. To the families of the victims my deep sympathy, together with the feeling of proximity to the worker who is currently in the Reanimation department at the Polyclinic Hospital of Palermo". To write it on X is the president of the Council, Giorgia Meloni. "She made full light on this tragedy," concludes Premier.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Mattarella, ennesima and unacceptable massacre at work
&nbsp; The President of the Republic, Sergio Mattarella, visiting New York, expressed his condolence for the serious tragedy on the work that caused the death of five workers in Casteldaccia, in the province of Palermo. "Auspico - he said - is made full light on the dynamics of the accident. But the unacceptable yet-year-old massacres at work, just a few days from May 1st, must strongly repropose the need for a common commitment that must concern the social forces, entrepreneurs and the institutions prepared".
&nbsp;

