AGI -&nbsp;Today "we implement the economic resources of fishery entrepreneurs and we create a fund available to the commissioner > to ensure all interventions in support of our entrepreneurs", to the grips with the diffusion of blue crab. The Minister for Agriculture, and Food Sovereignty and Forests, Francesco Lollobrigida, intervened in connection with 'Future North Direction', talking about one of the topics at the center of today's Council of Ministers meeting, the Agriculture Decree that provides measures also for the emergency blue crab.'
&nbsp;
"Last year there was an abundance of blue crab, the situation is emerging at this time," said the minister, explaining that the government intervened "with the support of entrepreneurs" to provide him with "struments to counter blue crab and to try to market > this product which has a particularly high value especially in some nations like the U.S. and rich markets".
&nbsp;
"I say this, the intervention must be wider," said Lollobrigida, explaining that it concerns not only our country. "We asked for Europe's involvement because &nbsp; the whole question concerns the Mediterranean and can affect Greece, Albania" That's why we called for a European strategy." And at the same time "we act with a commissarial intervention", this because&nbsp;"The commissioner can intervene with actions to solve the problem more quickly. It doesn't take a few days because&nbsp; the delay is ten years." &nbsp;

